name: I Miss You
wikiSummary: Released Feb 1997 (from Post) & toured that same year, see I Miss You (Live 1997). "It's not about anyone in particular because it's about someone I haven't met. It's like a word game: "I miss you but I haven't met you yet - It's about looking forward to something that hasn't happened." (Record Collector, Aug '02). The animated surreal & sexual music video was made by John Kricfalusi (of Spümcø, best known for the Ren & Stimpy cartoons, admired by Björk).
wikiText: Released Feb 1997 (from Post) & toured that same year, see I Miss You (Live 1997). "It's not about anyone in particular because it's about someone I haven't met. It's like a word game: "I miss you but I haven't met you yet - It's about looking forward to something that hasn't happened." (Record Collector, Aug '02). The animated surreal & sexual music video was made by John Kricfalusi (of Spümcø, best known for the Ren & Stimpy cartoons, admired by Björk). She has ginger hair in animated & live parts, of the video. One of Kricfalusi's characters, Jimmy the Idiot Boy, joins her during various parts of the video. Another of his characters, George Liquor, makes a cameo in one scene. User-contributed text is available under the Creative Commons By-SA License and may also be available under the GNU FDL.
